T1  - Methodological Orientations and Management Theory: An Analysis of Academic Opinion
AU  - Duncan, W. Jack
Y1  - 1970/09/01
PY  - 1970
DA  - 1970/09/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/254969
DO  - 10.5465/254969
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 337
EP  - 348
VL  - 13
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - In view of the contemporary emphasis on specific research techniques, it is interesting to note how little attention has been directed toward the more general problem of methodology in management theory. The findings of this study indicate an almost universal agreement among management professors concerning the virtues of empirical methods. Opinions regardings the ultimate objectives or goals of administrative theory, however, are far less unanimous.
