TY  - JOUR
T1  - The Use of PPBS In a Public System of Higher Education: “Is it Cost-Effective?”
AU  - Dyer, James S.
Y1  - 1970/09/01
PY  - 1970
DA  - 1970/09/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/254965
DO  - 10.5465/254965
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 285
EP  - 299
VL  - 13
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - This paper presents a qualitative discussion of the potential ?costs? and ?benefits? associated with the use of PPBS in a public system of higher education. The ?costs,? both monetary and nonmonetary, resulting from the introduction of PPBS are acknowledged to be significant. However, the inadequacies of existing budgeting techniques as aids in decision-making and problems of resource allocation are severe. These limitations are identified and discussed. The potential contributions of PPBS in these areas are then considered.
